data.description: Indulge in luxury with this exquisite home that radiates opulence and sophistication! Nestled in the prestigious Prairie Ridge subdivision, this two-story gem showcases a main floor adorned with elegance, boasting a luxurious primary bedroom suite. Approaching the residence, marvel at the regal curb appeal, featuring a custom stone mailbox and refined landscaping that sets the stage for the grandeur within. The entrance is breathtaking, with a dramatic two-story foyer adorned with a brand-new chandelier and an open staircase, signaling the excellence that awaits. On the main floor, relish the luxury of some raised 10-foot ceilings, complemented by pristine white trim and doors. Entertain with flair in the formal living room, open parlor, family room, and spacious dining room that accommodates up to 12 guests, adding a touch of glamour to every gathering. The living room seamlessly connects to the family room, showcasing a remodeled floor-to-ceiling tiled fireplace—an exquisite focal point that matches the kitchen's floor-to-ceiling tile work. The parlor, currently used as a music and sitting room, provides an inviting space, all connected by seamless wood plank floors for a custom feel. The chef's dream kitchen boasts ample modern white cabinetry, newer quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and an exquisite tile backsplash extending to the ceiling for added grandeur. A center island with seating and a breakfast nook enhance the space, creating a perfect blend of functionality and style. The floor plan, with clearly defined spaces, flows seamlessly and features custom colonial pillars for a touch of prestige. A mudroom with custom tile and storage, doubling as a laundry room with hookups, adds practicality. The main floor primary bedroom is a sanctuary of luxury, spanning 320 square feet, with a previously remodeled en suite bathroom and a walk-in closet. Indulge in the spa-like en suite bathroom with ceramic wood plank flooring, a double vanity with a Quartz countertop, a Whirlpool tub, and a custom-tiled walk-in shower. Upstairs, discover three oversized bedrooms and a hall bathroom with a Quartz double sink vanity and ceramic tile wood plank flooring. The backyard invites relaxation with a newer composite deck and a concrete patio featuring a raised seating area, perfect for outdoor gatherings. This residence is not only visually stunning but also a wise investment. The roof was replaced in 2021, and the central air was upgraded in 2019. The massive basement offers additional space for your personal touch, along with an already finished laundry room. Situated in the sought-after Rockton and Hononegah school districts, it benefits from a low 9.3% tax rate—a rare find in today's market. Skip the hassle of building; this home offers unparalleled luxury at a fraction of the cost. Your future awaits!
